---
title: zero-dependency-crypto-in-ltl
author: bad-antics
date: 2026-04-05
abstract: This document presents the design and implementation of the Lateralus built-in cryptographic library, showcasing its use of ChaCha20-Poly1305, BLAKE2b, HMAC, and PBKDF2. We provide correctness proofs and discuss tradeoffs and design rationale.

---

## Introduction

The security requirements for a cryptographic library are stringent. In the context of Lateralus, we sought to create a library with zero dependencies on external libraries or frameworks. Our solution leverages established cryptographic primitives while introducing novel optimizations. In this paper, we will outline the design and implementation of our library, focusing on correctness proofs, tradeoffs, and design rationales.

## Section 1: Overview of Implemented Primitives

We implemented the following cryptographic primitives:

*   ChaCha20-Poly1305 (CSP) for authenticated encryption
*   BLAKE2b (BLAKE2) for hash functions
*   HMAC (Keyed-Hash Message Authentication Code) for message authentication
*   PBKDF2 (Password-Based Key Derivation Function 2) for password-based key derivation

### Section 1.1: ChaCha20-Poly1305

